it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.shorts

Interface Short2LongMap.FastEntrySet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<Short2LongMap.Entry>, Iterable<Short2LongMap.Entry>, ObjectCollection<Short2LongMap.Entry>, ObjectIterable<Short2LongMap.Entry>, ObjectSet<Short2LongMap.Entry>, Set<Short2LongMap.Entry>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Short2LongSortedMap.FastSortedEntrySet
    Enclosing interface:
    Short2LongMap

    public static interface Short2LongMap.FastEntrySet
extends ObjectSet<Short2LongMap.Entry>
    An entry set providing fast iteration.

    In some cases (e.g., hash-based classes) iteration over an entry set requires the creation of a large number of Map.Entry objects. Some fastutil maps might return entry set objects of type FastEntrySet: in this case, fastIterator() will return an iterator that is guaranteed not to create a large number of objects, possibly by returning always the same entry (of course, mutated).
